    "Roughly one million of these were found during source detection in regions given externally or identified as containing a bright source, and the remaining ones were ingested as known point sources to monitor.",
    "In total, roughly 150 000 alerts were generated.",
    "Out of these, we identified several time critical events, which were published mostly as Astronomer's Telegrams (Rutledge 1998).",
    "The first such event occurred shortly after the begin of the survey on December 31, 2019 and was caused by a bright, and yet otherwise unidentified, X-ray transient designated SRGt J123822.3-253206 with a flux of 2 × 10 -10 erg s -1 cm -2 in the 0.2-10 keV band (see Fig.",
    "C.1, Wilms et al. 2020)."
